title: The Star Online maintains position as Malaysia’s top news portal
text:
PETALING JAYA: The Star Online has retained its position as the top news portal in the country. 
According to a report by the Malaysian Digital Association (MDA), The Star Online maintained pole for the month of November 2016.
Based on data from comScore Me­­dia Metrix, the report showed that The Star Online ranked ninth among the top 20 local web domains most visited on desktop computers in Malaysia, with 705,000 visitors.
The report also showed that The Star’s website www.thestar.com.my ranked ahead of other news portals including Malaysiakini (ranked 10th) and Harian Metro (19th).
Maybank’s online banking portal maybank2u.com.my remained in the first place with 3.9 million unique visitors, followed by CIMB’s banking portal cimbclicks.com.my and  AirAisa.com.my.
Websites that were not in the top 20 in Oct but managed to break through in Nov include Lynk.my, Cocomy.net and Maxis.com.
The Star Online was also the top news portal in March and June , according to an earlier report released by MDA.
comScore Media Metrix is the official Internet audience measurement currency of the MDA.
Released monthly, the MDA report measures web activity among Malaysian Internet users.
International traffic is not included in the report.
